I filled out another response for 61B a while ago after Heather said:

&#34;No, seriously. There are people who will listen to you. You need to go farther on if you feel that you have a legitimate concern that isn&#39;t being addressed. The 61C issue has reached a number of faculty in the department and is being reviewed. For 61B last semester, I would be sure to start with Josh Hug. Then you can talk to Michael Ball, as the Grievance Officer. Obviously he can&#39;t handle all cases of students having a homework they feel is misgraded, but if you&#39;re a DSP student, and you feel that your needs weren&#39;t met, you need to say something. If there&#39;s a larger issue that needs to be seen to you can also use the form that John Canny sent out this week for making reports.&#34;


This is in response to my concerns about exams being graded harshly.
